24 September 2014The Inter-Ministerial Task Team on the Nigerian Tragedy will host a media briefing led by Minister Jeff Radebe to give updates on the process of body identification and repatriation of mortal remains of South Africans who perished following the collapse of a building at the Synagogue Church of All Nations in Lagos, Nigeria.The details of the briefing are as follows:Date: 24 September 2014 Time: 16h00 Venue: GCIS Head Office, Tshedimosetso House , 1035 Francis Baard Street, Hatfield, Pretoria NB: There will be a video link-up to Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Parliament, Cape TownRSVP: Tshegofatso Modubu (Pretoria) Cell: 083 276 0786 E-mail: Tshegofatso@gcis.gov.za Mzimasi Ngqelu (Cape Town) Cell: 076 904 3557 E-mail: mzi@gcis.gov.zaEnquiries: Phumla Williams Cell: 083 501 0139Issued by: Government Communication and Information System (GCIS)